<h1>From C. W. F. Dumas</h1>
<div class="docbody" xml:lang="fra">
<div class="opener"><table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Monsieur,</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">Lahaie 12<span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">e</span> Dec. 1782</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>Une seconde Lettre reue ce matin de Mr. Van Arp, dAmst. mengage  crire tout de suite;<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0071-fn-0001" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0071-fn-0001-ptr">1</a> voici ce quil me dit en Hollandois.</p>
<span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-14-02-pb-0122">[122<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-14/ADMS-06-14-02-pb-0122.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>
<p>Je vous suis oblig de votre prompitude  crire  S. E. Mr. Adams. Je suis seulement mortifi de devoir vous donner une nouvelle peine  ce sujet: cest que le Cap<span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">ne.</span> Steph. Crack a d renoncer au comandement du Vaisseau le <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Fearnot</span> Brig  2 ponts du port come dans ma prcedente, lequel sera comand par le Cap<span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">ne.</span> Raphal Simpson de Boston, pour faire voile au plutt pour Boston, mont de 10 Canons, Equipage &amp; munitions de guerre en consquence, selon laffiche ci-jointe. Cest donc sous le nom du Cap. Raphal Simpson de Boston que S. E. aura la bont de mettre le Passeport demand.</p>
<p>Je crois quil sest agi ce matin du Ministre que cette rep. enverra au Congrs. Laffaire de la <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Conjuration des Cocardes</span>, &amp; plusieurs autres qui toient dj sur le tapis, fait que par discrtion je me suis abstenu dimportuner nos amis, fort occups, &amp; que je patiente jusqu Dimanche, pour savoir ce qui se sera pass. En attendant, Mad<span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">e.</span> Dumas, qui avec ma fille, vous prsente ses honneurs, non contente des Serrures &amp; Verroux qui assurent la porte de lhtel, la fait fortifier en dedans dune chane, que lon tend toutes les nuits.</p>
<p>Une cinquime Ville, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Hindelopen</span>, en Frise, a suivi lexemple de Dokkum &amp; des 3 autres dont jai dj fait mention.</p>
<p>Je Suis toujours avec le respectueux attachement qui vous est vou, Monsieur, / De V. Exc<span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">e.</span> / le trs-humble &amp; trs / obissant serviteur,</p>
<div class="closer"><p class="signed">Dumas</p>
</div>
<div class="postscript"><p>Sil ny a pas de forte raison, qui empchent les prliminaires signs dtre publis; il seroit  souhaiter quils le fussent dans ce pays, o lon abuse du serment extorqu avant de les comuniquer, pour laisser la nation dans lerreur, malgr ce que nous pouvons dire pour la rassurer, dans des doutes qui linquietent encore.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0071-fn-0002" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0071-fn-0002-ptr">2</a></p></div>
</div>
<div class="translation">
<h2><span class="hi-all-small-caps" style="font-variant: small-caps; text-transform: lowercase;">Translation</span></h2>
<div class="opener"><table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Sir</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">The Hague, 12 December 1782</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>A second letter, received this morning from Mr. Van Arp in Amsterdam obliges me to write to you at once.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0071-fn-0001" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0071-fn-0001-ptr">1</a> Here is what he says in Dutch:</p>
<p>I am obliged to you for writing so promptly to his excellency Mr. Adams. However, I am mortified at having to trouble you again on this subject: Capt. Stephen Crack has had to resign his command of the ship <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Fear-not</span>, a brig of two decks and the burden as previously described. It will now be commanded by Capt. Raphael Simpson of Boston. It is to sail as soon as possible for Boston, mounting ten cannons, with the requisite crew and ammunition, as detailed in the attached manifest. His excellency should therefore please make out the passport we requested in the name of Capt. Raphael Simpson of Boston.</p>
<span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-14-02-pb-0123">[123<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-14/ADMS-06-14-02-pb-0123.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>
<p>I believe that this morning the question of who the republic will send to Congress as its minister was raised. Because of the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Cockade Conspiracy</span> and several other matters already on the agenda, I discreetly refrained from bothering our friends, who are extremely busy, and I am waiting until Sunday to see what transpires. Meanwhile Madame Dumas, not content with the locks and bolts protecting the door to the house, has had it additionally fortified with a chain on the inside, which we attach every night. She and my daughter send you their respects.</p>
<p>A fifth town, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Hindelopen</span> in Friesland, has followed the examples of Dokkum and the three others I already mentioned.</p>
<p>With continuing respect and devotion I remain, sir, your excellencys very humble and very obedient servant</p>
   <div class="closer"><p class="signed">Dumas</p></div>
<div class="postscript"><p>If there is no compelling reason to prevent the preliminaries from being made public, it would be a good idea for them to be published in this country, where the oath of secrecy is being abused, leaving the nation misinformed and, despite all we can say to reassure it, in a state of worried uncertainty.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0071-fn-0002" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0071-fn-0002-ptr">2</a></p></div>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0071-sn">
   <p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ recipients copy (A recipients copy is assumed to be in the hand of the signer unless it is otherwise described.) ]">RC</abbr> (<span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers</span>); internal address: Paris  Son Exc<span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">e.</span> Mr. Adams.</p>
</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0071-fn-0001-ptr" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0071-fn-0001">1</a>
   <p>For Van Arps first letter as well as the other matters mentioned by Dumas here, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-14-02-0068" class="document">Dumas letter of 10 Dec.</a>, above; but see also <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-14-02-0081" class="document"><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s reply of 19 Dec.</a>, below.</p>
</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0071-fn-0002-ptr" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0071-fn-0002">2</a>
   <p>For <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s initial reaction to Dumas proposal to print the preliminary treaty, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-14-02-0081" class="document">his reply of 19 Dec.</a>; and for his later opinion, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-14-02-0158" class="document">his 7 Feb. 1783 letter to Dumas</a>, both below.</p>
</div>
